1512
01:24:14,705 --> 01:24:16,900
-请坐下，恭喜你 -谢谢、谢谢
-Please, sit. Congratulations. -Thanks. Thanks.

1513
01:24:16,974 --> 01:24:18,305
是哪个幸运的家伙？
Who's the lucky guy?

1514
01:24:18,375 --> 01:24:20,104
-山姆诺斯 -喔
-Sam Knowles. -Okay.

1515
01:24:20,177 --> 01:24:22,236
但他基本上已经出局了
But he's basically out of the picture.

1516
01:24:22,313 --> 01:24:24,338
-他没上榜喔？ -嗯
-He didn't make the cut, huh? -Yeah.

1517
01:24:24,415 --> 01:24:29,648
我也不需要男人，  一直都不是很需要
Well, I don't need a guy. I never really did.

1518
01:24:29,720 --> 01:24:32,018
你应该算是最亲密的吧
You were about the closest I ever got.

1519
01:24:32,089 --> 01:24:36,185
真的，  我跟你在一起时曾想过 “就是他了”
No, really, when I was with you, I thought, "This is it."

1520
01:24:36,260 --> 01:24:37,557
但我搞砸了
But I screwed it up.

1521
01:24:37,628 --> 01:24:40,461
-你没有 -我有，  绝对有
-No, you didn't. -I did. I so did.

1522
01:24:41,065 --> 01:24:42,555
听著
Listen,

1523
01:24:42,633 --> 01:24:46,569
我星期天要办个小聚会
I'm having a little party Sunday.

1524
01:24:47,371 --> 01:24:49,498
-我要你来 -天啊
-I want you to come. -Oh, boy.

1525
01:24:50,141 --> 01:24:52,803
下午四点，  不准不到
4:00. No excuses.

1526
01:24:52,004 --> 01:24:53,045
(SIGHING)

1527
01:24:53,944 --> 01:24:56,811
你要来吗？拜托嘛？
Will you come? Please?

1528
01:24:56,881 --> 01:24:58,872
我看看赶不赶得上
You know, I'll see if I can make it.

1529
01:24:58,949 --> 01:25:01,679
-我很希望你来 -我会到的
-I really want you to. -I'll make it.

1530
01:25:01,752 --> 01:25:04,186
我想跟被我伤害过的人言归于好
I want to make amends with anyone I ever hurt.

1531
01:25:04,255 --> 01:25:07,747
我估计要花上九个月
And I figure it'll take about nine months,

1532
01:25:07,825 --> 01:25:09,656
时间上刚好
which is perfect timing.

1533
01:25:11,362 --> 01:25:13,592
-她要走了，  再见 -再见
-And she's off. Bye. -Bye-bye.

1534
01:25:15,799 --> 01:25:17,096
威廉海约
William Hayes.

1535
01:25:17,168 --> 01:25:20,228
-爸，  或许这主意不是很好 -什么？
-Dad, maybe this wasn't such a good idea. - What?

1536
01:25:20,304 --> 01:25:24,070
跟我说这故事，  这爱情悬疑故事
Telling me this story, this mystery love story.

1537
01:25:25,342 --> 01:25:28,743
-要是我不喜欢我妈怎么办？ -你当然会喜欢你妈
-What if I don't like who my mom is? -Of course you'll like who your mom is.

1538
01:25:28,812 --> 01:25:31,440
你不用等太久，  因为当晚…
And you don't have to wait long to find out, because that very night...

1539
01:25:31,515 --> 01:25:34,416
是夏曼，  对不对？而你不是我生父
It's Summer, isn't it? And you're not my father.

1540
01:25:34,485 --> 01:25:36,248
难怪你不想跟她在一起
No wonder you didn't want to be with her.

1541
01:25:36,320 --> 01:25:39,653
放轻松点，玛雅，  这只是个故事
Take it easy, Maya. It's just a story.

1542
01:25:41,091 --> 01:25:43,821
而且有快乐的结局
And this one has a happy ending.

1543
01:25:43,894 --> 01:25:46,260
怎么会有快乐结局？
How does it have a happy ending?

1544
01:25:46,330 --> 01:25:50,733
你跟我妈，  不管她是谁 你们要离婚了
You and my mom, whoever she is, you're getting divorced.

1545
01:25:51,702 --> 01:25:54,034
有什么好快乐的？
What's the happy in that?

1546
01:25:58,475 --> 01:26:00,443
好吧，  你知道吗？我们该停了
Okay, you know what? I think we should stop now.

1547
01:26:00,511 --> 01:26:02,069
不！
No!

1548
01:26:04,748 --> 01:26:06,841
来杯茶好吗？
Then how about a nice cup of tea?

1549
01:26:07,418 --> 01:26:10,751
你想的话，  我们继续讲故事，  如何？
If you want, I'll still continue with the story. Does that sound good?

1550
01:26:10,821 --> 01:26:12,789
-玛雅？ -好
-Maya? -Okay.

1551
01:26:19,196 --> 01:26:20,754
爸？
Dad?

1552
01:26:22,499 --> 01:26:27,630
我真不敢相信你又抽烟又喝酒 还那么随便
I can't believe you smoked and drank and were such a slut.

1553
01:26:30,641 --> 01:26:32,541
但我还是爱你
But I still love you.

1554
01:26:37,734 --> 01:26:38,901
(SIGHS)

1555
01:26:39,903 --> 01:26:41,571
(KETTLE WHISTLING)

1556
01:27:35,706 --> 01:27:37,037
谢了
Thanks.

1557
01:27:37,107 --> 01:27:39,337
好的、好的
All right. All right.

1558
01:27:39,410 --> 01:27:42,470
不、不，  先别吃，要先到我们的板凳
No, no. Don't eat it yet! Not till we get to our bench.

1559
01:27:43,347 --> 01:27:44,837
你心情不错
You're in a good mood.

1560
01:27:44,915 --> 01:27:48,908
我想我从故事中发现了我妈是谁
Well, I think I discovered who my mom is in the story.

1561
01:27:48,986 --> 01:27:51,011
-真的？ -真的
-Really? -Really.

1562
01:27:51,955 --> 01:27:54,219
-是谁？ -不告诉你
-Well, who is it? -Not telling.

1563
01:27:55,993 --> 01:27:58,291
我们最后一次见到威廉海约时
So the last time we saw William Hayes,

1564
01:27:58,362 --> 01:28:01,923
他刚发现他的至爱，  艾波霍夫曼
he had just discovered that the woman he truly loved, April Hoffman,

1565
01:28:02,032 --> 01:28:03,932
爱上了别人
was in love with another man.

1566
01:28:03,195 --> 01:28:04,278
(WILLIAM GASPS)

1567
01:28:04,335 --> 01:28:06,428
我知道，很耸动
I know. Shocking.

1568
01:28:07,404 --> 01:28:09,429
在这期间，  他接受了邀约
Meanwhile, he accepted an invitation

1569
01:28:09,506 --> 01:28:12,498
去他前女友夏曼哈德尼家
to the home of his ex-girlfriend, Summer Hartley,

1570
01:28:12,576 --> 01:28:16,535
她若真是我妈，  我就逃去加拿大
who, if she does turn out to be my mother, I'm running away to Canada.

1571
01:28:16,613 --> 01:28:18,376
我不是说笑
I'm not kidding.

1572
01:28:25,989 --> 01:28:28,423
-他去年走了 -嗯
-He died last year. -Yeah.

1573
01:28:28,492 --> 01:28:31,120
-你听说了？ -我在《纽约时报》上有看到
-You heard? -I read about it in The Times.

1574
01:28:31,195 --> 01:28:32,890
-嗯 -嗯
-Yeah. -Yeah.

1575
01:28:32,963 --> 01:28:35,397
-天啊，  在办公室里，  心脏病吗？ -嗯
-God. Died in his office. Heart attack? -Yeah.

1576
01:28:35,466 --> 01:28:39,527
我一直以为他会走得很戏剧性
I always imagined that he'd make a more theatrical exit.

1577
01:28:39,603 --> 01:28:43,095
他们没说他当时 跟系主任的女儿在沙发上
What they didn't say was he was on the couch with the dean's daughter.

1578
01:28:43,173 --> 01:28:45,141
-老天 -开玩笑的
-Jesus. -I'm kidding.

1579
01:28:45,943 --> 01:28:51,381
事实上他是一个人 好几个小时后才被工友发现
Actually, he was completely alone and it was hours before the janitor found him.

1580
01:28:52,349 --> 01:28:54,943
-要喝点什么？ -抱歉
-You want a drink? -I'm sorry.

1581
01:28:55,018 --> 01:28:57,748
-你一定很想念他 -我是啊
-You must miss him. -I do, yeah.

1582
01:28:58,655 --> 01:28:59,781
这是给你的
These are for you.

1583
01:28:59,857 --> 01:29:02,291
-喔，  威尔 -嗯
-Oh, Will. -Yeah.

1584
01:29:04,428 --> 01:29:06,259
好美
They're beautiful.

1585
01:29:08,365 --> 01:29:09,992
你也是
So are you.

1586
01:29:11,969 --> 01:29:13,937
-夏曼 -威尔
-Summer. -Will.

1587
01:29:14,004 --> 01:29:15,767
别闹我
Don't mess with me.

1588
01:29:15,839 --> 01:29:17,170
我知道你想要干嘛
I can see where you're going with this.

1589
01:29:17,241 --> 01:29:20,233
再过一会，  你就会说句迷死人的话
In a second, you're gonna say something impossibly charming.

1590
01:29:20,310 --> 01:29:22,244
-真的？ -嗯，  会很棒
-Really? -Yeah. It's gonna be great.

1591
01:29:22,312 --> 01:29:25,304
然后你会完全迷倒我 我们都知道结局会是什么
And then you're gonna sweep me off my feet and we all know where that's going.

1592
01:29:25,382 --> 01:29:27,976
-女孩难道就不能想念男孩吗？ -你也知道没好下场
-Can't a girl miss a guy? -And you know that's gonna end badly.

1593
01:29:28,051 --> 01:29:29,678
她可以
Yeah, she can,

1594
01:29:29,853 --> 01:29:32,447
但我真的没时间承受那种痛
but I just don't really have time for the pain.

1595
01:29:32,523 --> 01:29:36,482
-不如就略过这些吧？ -好
-So let's just skip all that, why don't we? -Okay.

1596
01:29:37,394 --> 01:29:39,021
很公平
Fair enough.

1597
01:29:39,596 --> 01:29:40,961
能做朋友吗？
Can we be friends?

1598
01:29:41,031 --> 01:29:43,022
-好！好 -好
-Yeah! Yeah. -Yeah.

1599
01:29:43,100 --> 01:29:45,728
-一言为定？好 -就这样，  好
-Shake on it? Okay. -Let's do that. All right.

1600
01:29:48,705 --> 01:29:50,434
你知道吗？
You know what?

1601
01:29:52,743 --> 01:29:55,143
我想让你见个人
There's someone here I want you to meet.

1602
01:29:56,246 --> 01:29:58,737
嗯，  跟我来
Yeah. Come with me.

1603
01:29:58,816 --> 01:30:00,113
是我的旧爱
They're an old flame of mine,

1604
01:30:00,184 --> 01:30:04,416
我觉得你们俩应该很聊得来
and I think you guys are really gonna, you know, hit it off.

1605
01:30:08,258 --> 01:30:09,885
艾蜜莉
Emily.

1606
01:30:12,095 --> 01:30:14,222
我把这些插起来
I'm gonna put these in some water.

1607
01:30:17,568 --> 01:30:19,729
-你看来… -你看来…
-You look... -You look...

1608
01:30:19,706 --> 01:30:20,790
(EMILY CHUCKLING)

1609
01:30:20,904 --> 01:30:22,667
你看来很好
You look great.

1610
01:30:23,574 --> 01:30:26,737
-你怎么在纽约？ -我住在这
-Why are you in New York? -I live here.

1611
01:30:26,810 --> 01:30:30,268
我在市政府教育部做事
I took a job with the city education department.

1612
01:30:30,347 --> 01:30:32,815
-我有打给你 -我知道
-I called you. -I know.

1613
01:30:32,883 --> 01:30:35,408
-我一直想回你 -骗子
-I've been meaning to call you back. -Liar.

1614
01:30:36,253 --> 01:30:37,914
-我弄丢了你的号码 -当然
-I had lost your number. -Of course.

1615
01:30:37,988 --> 01:30:40,422
-是真的，  你知道吗？ -威尔…
-No, it's true. You know what? -Will...

1616
01:30:40,491 --> 01:30:42,356
好吧，现在就给我你的电话
Okay, give me your number, right now.

1617
01:30:42,426 --> 01:30:46,385
我马上输入我的手机里 这样就永远不会掉了，  好吗？
I'm gonna put it in my cell phone, and that way I'm never gonna lose it, okay?

1618
01:30:47,965 --> 01:30:53,267
我的号码是212-664-7665
My number is 212-664-7665.

1619
01:30:53,337 --> 01:30:57,103
6、6、5，  你看？我输入了 现在就不会掉了
Six, six, five. See? Now I got it. And I'm never gonna lose it again.

1620
01:30:56,493 --> 01:30:58,244
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

